Disable KASLR in cepheus_user_defconfig to fix kallsyms relative mode failure.

The Bootlin aarch64-glibc toolchain links the kernel at a fixed address
(0xffffff8008080000) that is out of range for CONFIG_KALLSYMS_BASE_RELATIVE
encoding. KASLR has no effect without bootloader entropy support anyway.
Disabling RANDOMIZE_BASE causes KALLSYMS_BASE_RELATIVE to also be cleared,
resolving the "relative symbol value out of range in relative mode" linker
error during vmlinux assembly.

CONFIG_RANDOMIZE_BASE=n in the config fragment is overridden by silentoldconfig
because the base defconfig explicitly sets it; patching the defconfig directly
ensures it survives kconfig fixup.

--- a/arch/arm64/configs/cepheus_user_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/cepheus_user_defconfig
@@ -82,7 +82,7 @@
 CONFIG_CP15_BARRIER_EMULATION=y
 CONFIG_SETEND_EMULATION=y
 # CONFIG_ARM64_VHE is not set
-CONFIG_RANDOMIZE_BASE=y
+# CONFIG_RANDOMIZE_BASE is not set
 # CONFIG_EFI is not set
 CONFIG_BUILD_ARM64_APPENDED_DTB_IMAGE=y
 CONFIG_BUILD_ARM64_UNCOMPRESSED_KERNEL=y
